/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/External-Board-Reviews/042026-schema-v12/r2-brief.md:226:**On Q1 (coordinated vs staged):** D-8 is not purely additive. The field-name renames in D-8 touch `phase_1_raw_capture.repo_metadata` and `pre_flight`, which are also what compute.py reads to produce advisory scorecard signals for D-7. If you do D-8 first, compute.py's input signatures change, and the D-7 advisory cell shape depends on those same fields. Running both together avoids fixture regeneration twice and avoids a half-migrated state where the harness is schema-canonical but compute.py still reads V1.1-named fields.
